{"key":"processedPost-17183874","value":{"id":17183874,"first":17183722,"last":17197926,"when":1352392085,"utime":"11/08/12 06:28 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />The changes I have made in anticipation include plastic over the windows<br /></blockquote><br /><br />As someone who heats exclusively with a wood stove, I'll advise you should never cover the windows with plastic or anything else which will impede the influx of fresh air.&nbsp; A wood stove needs a supply of fresh air for combustion.<br /><br />The answer is insulation.&nbsp; I live in a much colder climate than you do and my wood stove keeps the whole house at 80F all winter, even when it's -40 outdoors.&nbsp; It also helps to have a ceiling fan to distribute the warm air around the house.<br /><br />For the time being, you can make a small room for growing and insulate it well.&nbsp; Place a small electric heater in the area.<br />RR","title":"Re: Cold house...ways to increase temp","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}